  {\section{#1}\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{#1}}

\section{Introduction}
Some text here.

\sectionwithtoc{Methods}
Methods section content.

\section{Results}
Results section content.

\subsection{Data Analysis}
Data analysis details.

\sectionwithtoc{Discussion}
Discussion section content.

\section{Conclusion}
Conclusion section content.

% Ensure all sections are added to ToC if using custom macros
\addtocounter{section}{-1} % Example adjustment if needed after custom macros

\newpage % Start fresh on a new page after ToC

% Main content continues here...

\section{Appendices}
Appendices content.

\section{References}
\bibliographystyle{plain}
\bibliography{yourbibliography}

\end{document}
```

**Additional Notes and Customization (with `hyperref` and `tocloft`):**

1. **Basic ToC with `hyperref`:**
   ```latex
   \usepackage{hyperref}
   \hypersetup{
     pdfkeywords={...}, % Add your keywords
     colorlinks=true,
     linkcolor=blue,
     filecolor=magenta,  % Links to files (like bibliography)
     urlcolor=cyan       % Links to URLs
   }
   ```

2. **Advanced ToC with `tocloft`:**
   ```latex
   \usepackage{tocloft}
   \renewcommand{\cftsecfont}{\bfseries} % Change section title font in ToC
   \renewcommand{\cftsecpagefont}{\itshape} % Change section page number font
   \setlength{\cftsecnumwidth}{3.5cm} % Adjust section number width
   ```

3. **Automating Section Inclusion (if needed beyond custom macros):**
   ```latex
   % Loop or list approach for sections (advanced)
   \begin{document}
     \tableofcontents
     \newpage

     \foreach \sectiontitle in {Introduction, Methods, Results, Discussion, Conclusion, Appendices} {
       \section{\sectiontitle}
       \addcontentsline{toc}{section}{\sectiontitle}
     }
   ```

This example demonstrates a straightforward approach with custom macros for automatic ToC generation, along with optional enhancements using `hyperref` and `tocloft`. Adjust the commands and structure according to your specific LaTeX document class (e.g., `article`, `book`, `report`).

